args: Open up and say aaah, Luccy!
Scrambled eggs, from my heart to your\nstomach! Yumtown, right?
Hee! Okay, try the apple salad next.\nHeeeere comes the dragon! Nyoooom!
Can't a guy stuff his face in peace?

*ahem* Luca? Chelsea? We are all
overcome with joy at your union, but
perhaps you might pay some mind to
your table manners.
Open up the cave, 'cause here comes\nthe dragon!
(*sigh* I'm in seriously deep here.\nGotta do something, and fast...)
You're probably wondering how I ended up\nin this mess, gettin' fed like a baby in front\nof all my pals. Well...
Me and Chelsea? MARRIED?!\nWhere the hell'd ya hear that?!
What, is it not true? Chelsea sent\nhandmade cards to everyone in the\nvillage announcing your engagement.
Rrgh... No, it's NOT true! She's just doin'\nwhatever the heck she wants!
Yeah, I kinda figured.\nWho'd wanna marry you?
Look, can you please just go spread\nthe word that this is all a big\nmisunderstanding? I'll go talk to Chelsea.

Ba-da, ba-doo, mixin' in some love,
it's my secret spice. Ba-doo, ba-dee,
Luccy's gonna love it 'cause I cooked
it twice!
Luccy! Perfect timing. Breakfast is\naaalmost ready.
Oh snap, that looks gr—wait, no!
Look, I gotta clear something up. When\nI asked you to come live at the Halidom,\nthat was NOT a marriage proposal.
Awww, Luccy, you're so CUTE when you're\njoking.

I might've given you the wrong idea, and
I'm sorry about that. But I want to be very
clear: I was NOT saying we should get
married. At all.
You're my soul mate. We BELONG together.\nBut I guess we can't be? Or we just\nwon't be? I don't get it.
I feel weird. This world is weird.\nThis is all so WEIRD.
Maybe I'll just burn the whole thing down.\nStart all over. What's the point of a world\nwhere my Luccy hates me?
Burn it down. Burn it down, burn it DOWN,\nBURN IT DOWN BURN IT DOWN BURN IT\nDOWNBURNITDOWNBURNITDOWN...
...Yep. I'll burn it aaaaall down.\nStarting with this castle. Tee hee!
W-wait, Chelsea! I don't hate you!

But you said you didn't propose,
which means we're not getting
married, which means you HATE
me, which means I have to BURN—
Nothing needs to burn. Let's forget about\nthe burning, okay?
I had a dream, you know. I was feeding\nyou, just like Mama and Papa used to\nfeed me...
*sigh* Sure. Fine. You can feed me.
Really?! Yaaaaaaay!\nTee hee hee hee heeee!
She was super unstable. There was no telling\nwhat she woulda done if I'd left her like that.\nSo I just went along with her demands.
Hey, Luca. How're things with you'n\nChelsea?
Ranzal! So glad you asked. I need to\nunload, man! *blah blah blah*
That bad, huh? Want me to say something\nto her?
Sometimes all ya need is a third party\nto point somethin' out.
Would you really?! I'll take you out for...\nTEN dinners!
I woulda done it for free, but I'll take\nthat deal! Bwaaa ha ha!
Er, well, I might actually owe YOU\ndinner at this point. She uh, didn't\ntake it too well.
Only thing left is to take some time apart,\nI reckon. Here's what we're gonna do...
Okay, we managed to slip outta the\ncastle without her noticing. But what\nis this place?
This is my secret hideout in the woods.\nKnocked it together a while back\nas an emergency base of sorts.

Chelsea won't find ya out here, and even
if she does, she won't make it past the
door. So all ya gotta do is lie low till
her passion comes off the boil.
Gotcha. Hey, you wouldn't happen to have\nsomething to drink—
The hell happened to the door?!\nI triple-deadbolted it myself!

I always know where you are, Luccy.
That's the power of love! Oh, and
the power of love also lets me pick locks.
Tee hee!
Now, what are you doing all the way\nout here?
You weren't being NAUGHTY, were you?
I prepped this smokescreen in case\nsomething like this went down.\nQuick Luca, out the back door!
Looks that way. Let's hunker down at\nthe village nearby.
Wait... This arrowhead is dull.\nCould it be a mana-laced sleeping\narrow?
Phew... I think I actually gave her the slip.
BWAH! B-but you went the other way!
Yeah, that was a fake out. Now, tell me\nwhy you keep running away, love of my\nlife.
(There's no escaping her... Look's like\nI've got no choice.)
(If it goes badly, though, she'll torch the\nwhole castle...)
H-hey, can we talk some other time?
Ah, well, y'know, Ranzal's here, and I was\nreally hoping we could talk...alone.
EEEEEEE! A DATE! Just me and my Luccy!
Where should we go? What should I wear?\nShould I get a haircut? Ooo, what about\nmakeup? And...
Er... Okay, I guess we'll call it a date\nfor now.
(But can I even do it? Can I really clear up\nher misunderstanding?)
(Whatever. I have to settle this once\nand for all. I either get through to her,\nor die trying!)
Hee. A date. Tee hee! With my LUCCY!\nTEE HEE HEE HEEEEEE!
